name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(readxl)
library(readr)
library(RCurl)

library(shinylive)
library(httpuv)

ui <- fluidPage(
  titlePanel("Import d'un fichier Excel depuis GitHub"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      textInput(
        "url",
        "URL du fichier Excel (raw GitHub)",
        placeholder = "https://github.com/frees86/carrot/raw/refs/heads/main/source/CARROT_decision_tree.csv"
      ),
      actionButton("load", "Charger le fichier")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      h4("Your table:"),
      conditionalPanel(condition = "output.display == 'ON'",
                       textOutput("text"),
                       # tableOutput("table")
                       )
    )
  )
)

server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  values <- reactiveValues(
    df = data.frame,
    display = "OFF"
  )
  
  # The screen is either displayed or not:
  output$display <- reactive({ values$display })
  outputOptions(output, "display", suspendWhenHidden = FALSE) # This allow to use this as a condition in a conditionalPanel, even if the output is not shown
  

  observeEvent(input$load, {
    
    # req(input$url)
    # url <- input$url
    url <- "https://github.com/frees86/carrot/raw/refs/heads/main/source/CARROT_decision_tree.csv"
    req(url)
    # tmp <- tempfile(fileext = ".csv")
    tmp <- tempfile()
    download.file(url, tmp, mode = "wb")
    df <- read.csv(tmp, header = FALSE)
    
    # Here, we need to replace the special character "&" to display the table in R Shiny:
    df <- df %>%
      select(everything()) %>%
      dplyr::mutate_if(is.character, stringr::str_replace_all,
                       pattern = "&", replacement = "AND")
    values$df <- df
    values$display="ON"
  })
  
  # output$table <- renderTable({
  #   req(values$df)
  #   data.frame(values$df)
  # })
  
  output$text <- renderText({
    req(values$df)
    "Coucou !"
    # values$df[[1,4]]
  })
}

shinyApp(ui, server)
